ine Field|Everett]], [[Taranto-Grottaglie Airport|Grottaglie]], [[McConnell Air Force Base|Wichita\u2013McConnell AFB]]\n| [[FedEx Express]] | [[Piedmont Triad International Airport|Greensboro]], [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]], [[Nashville International Airport|Nashville]]\n| [[FedEx Feeder]] | [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]]\n| [[UPS Airlines]] | [[Columbia Metropolitian Airport|Columbia (SC)]], [[Greenville-Spartanburg International Airport|Greenville/Spartanburg]]\n}}\n\n==Statistics==\n===Airline market share===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|+ '''Largest Airlines at CHS (January 2019 \u2013 December 2019)'''<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\"/>\n|-\n!Rank\n!Airline\n!Passengers\n!Share\n|-\n|1\n|[[Delta Air Lines]]\n|1,041,000\n|22.01%\n|-\n|2\n|[[Southwest Airlines]]\n|729,000\n|15.42%\n|-\n|3\n|[[JetBlue]]\n|493,000\n|10.43%\n|-\n|4\n|[[PSA Airlines]]\n|435,000\n|9.20%\n|-\n|5\n|[[American Airlines]]\n|402,000\n|8.50%\n|-\n|6\n| Other\n|1,629,000\n|34.44%\n|-\n|}\n\n===Top destinations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ '''Busiest domestic routes from CHS (Jan 2019 \u2013 Dec 2019)'''<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\">{{cite web|url=http://www.transtats.bts.gov/airports.asp?pn=1&Airport=CHS&Airport_Name=Charleston,%20SC:%20Charleston%20AFB/International&carrier=FACTS |title=RITA &#124; BTS &#124; Transtats - CHS |publisher=Transtats.bts.gov|access-date=February 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! Rank\n! City\n! Passengers\n! Carriers\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Hartsfield\u2013Jackson Atlanta International Airport|Atlanta, Georgia]]\n| 463,310\n| Delta\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Charlotte Douglas International Airport|Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n| 252,040\n| American\n|-\n| 3\n| [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York\u2013JFK, New York]]\n| 169,370\n| Delta, JetBlue\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Baltimore/Washington International Airport|Baltimore, Maryland ]]\n| 131,540\n| Southwest\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Ronald Reagan Washington National A