ce Championships <br> Toyota Arena <br> Ontario, California|RD2=[[The X Cup]] <br> Location TBA|RD1-seed1=|RD1-team1= |RD1-seed2=|RD1-score1=|RD1-team2=|RD1-score=|RD1-seed3=|RD1-team3=|RD1-score3=|RD1-seed4=|RD1-team4=|RD1-score4=|RD2-team1=|RD2-score1=|RD2-team2=|RD2-score2=}}\n\n==References== \n{{reflist}} \n\n{{Legends Football League}} \n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2020 EXTFL season}} \n[[Category:2020 in American football|Extreme Football League]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|date=February 2020}}\n{{primary|date=February 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox league season\n|name=2020 Extreme Football League season\n|image=\n|season_start=April 11\n|season_end=August 15\n|playoffs_start=August 29\n|cup_title1=Eastern Conference Champions\n|cup_date1=\n|cup_champ1=\n|cup_title2=Western Conference Champions\n|cup_date2=\n|cup_champ2=\n|champion_title=[[The X Cup]]\n|champion_date=September 12, 2020\n|champion_site=\n|champion=\n|seasons_title= 2020\n|prev=[[2019 LFL US season|2019 (LFL)]] \n|next=[[2021 Extreme Football League season|2021]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2020 Extreme Football League season''' is the inaugural season of the [[Legends Football League|Extreme Football League]] (X League) in the [[United States]]. The league was formed on December 17, 2019, as a restructuring of the [[Legends Football League]].<ref name = \"X2020\">{{cite web |url=https://extfl.com/xwire/xwire/ |title=A NEW ERA IN WOMEN\u2019S EMPOWERMENT, THE X LEAGUE |website=extfl.com |date=December 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kentreporter.com/life/kent-to-have-team-in-rebranded-womens-indoor-football-league/ |title=Kent to have team in rebranded women\u2019s indoor football league |website=The Kent Reporter |date=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe season is slated to begin on April 11, 2020, and will conclude with the first-ever [[The X Cup|X Cup]], the league\u2019s championship game, on September 12, 2020.<ref name=schedule2020>{{cite web |url=https://extfl.com/schedule/ |title=X League 2020 Schedule |website=extfl.com |access-date=January 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Developments== \nThe[[Legends Football League]]'s [[Nashville Knights (football)|Nashville Knights]] missed several procedural deadlines required for participating in the 2020 season. As a result, the operations of the Knights were suspended by the league, and replaced by a new franchise, the [[Kansas City Force]] in January 2020.<ref>{{cite web |date=January 10, 2020 |url=https://extfl.com/xwire/x-league-statement-about-status-of-nashville-knights/ |title=X League Statement About Status of Nashville Knights |website=X League |access-date=January 14, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://extfl.com/xwire/x-league-announces-kansas-city-force-to-kickoff-2020-season/ |title=X LEAGUE ANNOUNCES KANSAS CITY FORCE TO KICKOFF 2020 SEASON |website=X League |date=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Standings==\n===Eastern Conference===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Team  \t\n! W\n! L\n! Pct\n! PF\n! PA\n! Net Pts\n! TD's\n! Home Record\n! Home Pct\n! Road Record\n! Road Pct\n|-\n| [[Atlanta Empire]] \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n|-\n| [[Chicago Blitz (2020)|Chicago Blitz]]\n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n|-\n| [[Kansas City Force]] \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n|-\n| [[Omaha Red Devils]] \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n|- \n|} \n\n===Western Conference=== \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Team  \t\n! W\n! L\n! Pct\n! PF\n! PA\n! Net Pts\n! TD's\n! Home Record\n! Home Pct\n! Road Record\n! Road Pct\n|-\n| [[Austin Sound]] \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n|- \n| [[Denver Rush]]\n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n|-\n| [[Los Angeles Black Storm]] \n| \n| \n| {{winpct|0|0}}\n| \n| \n| \n